Description: Finding the right answers to business accounting needs can be easy with a QuickBooks ProAdvisor consultant.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Finding the right answers to business accounting needs can be easy with a QuickBooks ProAdvisor consultant. While accountants, bookkeepers, advisors, consultants, management companies, and many other individuals tout services to help you set up and use QuickBooks more effectively, they may not have more than a basic understanding of the software. They may not even know how many useful QuickBooks features you're missing out on because QuickBooks is a surprisingly powerful accounting program. That is where the Quickbooks ProAdvisor consultant certification will come in handy. These professionals have a proven—by passing an exam—expertise in the use of Quickbooks. Different Certifications for ProAdvisor Consultants The Quickbooks ProAdvisor program identifies accounting professionals who can provide insight on the use of QuickBooks for a business or individual. The ProAdvisor can receive four different types of certifications demonstrating different levels of proficiency with QuickBooks and deeper mastery of QuickBooks industry editions. ProAdvisors may choose to take a certain number of hours of training—in-person in a classroom or online—or they can bypass any instruction and sit directly in the exam to get certified. QuickBooks Certification A QuickBooks ProAdvisor can receive a basic QuickBooks Certification. To get this certification, the ProAdvisor must successfully complete a certification exam. The exam covers topics such as QuickBooks installation, setup, recording transactions, and financial reporting. While candidates must score 85% to pass the exam, they get six chances to pass. If a candidate does not pass, they will be given the questions that were incorrect. Pro: This basic certification will give you some assurance that your ProAdvisor will have at least a basic proficiency with QuickBooks. Con: A ProAdvisor who holds only this certification may have learned how to pass an exam on QuickBooks through trial and error, not from a thorough understanding of the program. Remember that candidates get six attempts to pass the exam.

Description: Doing Science Anywhere
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, Inland Empire, West Coast
Full Description: At Anywhere Science we realize that science often happens outside of a laboratory and is routinely conducted by non-scientists. Every day, millions of test strips are used in order to make a myriad of chemistry of measurements. Many of these strips rely on user interpretation of colors or indicator lines in order to make estimations of analyte concentrations. For this reason, test strips are often viewed as “semi-quantitative” or even just simply “qualitative.” We realize that there exists tremendous opportunity to leverage the native capabilities of today’s smartphones with their massive install bases in order to convert “quick-and-dirty” test strips to powerful tools for rapid quantitative measurement. Our platform, LabStrip, is designed to transform the iPhone 4 series of smartphone into a deployable mobile laboratory. Each lot of test strips is meticulously calibrated in our laboratory using liquid standards of known value and the resultant calibration file is downloaded to the phone by scanning a QR code applied to each box of strips we sell. The user is able to make instant measurements in the field with no calibration required because we use the exact same LabStrip meters to calibrate and release product. We then feed the measurements from the LabStrip App to our cloud storage center, LabCloud, where it can be married with a host of other metadata for later data mining by the user. In addition to high-quality measurements, the iPhone 4 provides GPS location, date/time stamps, and the option to add annotations.

Description: Online Storefront Marketplace
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Hi, my name is Kathy Lester and I am CEO and Founder of Bidzinger.com(Home of the Anchor Stores) in Ellettsville, Indiana. My husband Daren and I are not new to the online buying and selling experience. We started selling on Ebay in December 2000 and grew shortly thereafter into Ebay Powersellers. This eventually helped us start our own enterprise and thus things got so busy for us that it turned into a full-time job. It wasn't until the last few years that things began to change on Ebay(hike in fees, feedback, how to sell, etc.)that gave us the idea to start our own online marketplace but without all the ridiculous dictations. We desire for Bidzinger to bring BACK the 'MAGIC' online auctions once had when Ebay first began. We WELCOME the mom and pop stores, the handcrafted items and things that once made Ebay fresh and very unique. We desire to see small business people grow with us into something big like Ebay had helped us to do 8 years ago. Somebody had asked me a few years ago when we first got started, "There are several auction sites out there that have started up and a lot of them are no longer around..what makes you think YOU are going to be any different?" Well, #1, we have put a lot of money on this website and with that thought, we have not just let this site go live without putting some of our own items on and continuously trying to build it up week by week along with other sellers that have joined with us. We have EVERY intention in becoming competitive and growing quickly! #2, we desire to also be like buyers and utilize our site just like anyone would if they owned a site or a store and that is to buy off of our own people. If we see something we could use for our business or around the house or perhaps something to purchase as a gift for someone at Christmas time, we are going to DO it! We desire to see unique sellers on our website making tons and tons of sales and doing great things with us! #3, we are going to and have been the last few months promoting and advertising Bidzinger in several different ways and things seem to be working great so far! #4, we are so sick and tired of sites like Ebay and others that think they have the right to get involved in the sellers business telling them what payments they can accept, how they need to ship, etc. We are not like that. You can accept payments HOWEVER you wish, ship to WHOMEVER you wish, and SELL to whomever you wish. That is YOUR decision; not ours. And that's the way it always should be. Join Bidzinger and become a part of our family! Registering is FREE, listing is FREE and browsing is FREE! 'Why should you LINGER when there's BIDZINGER?' http://www.bidzinger.com

Full Description: Address:  19 Holcomb Bridge Road Norcross, GA 30071 In 2015 anyone can shoot an HD video using a camcorder, a DSLR, or even a cell phone. We are not just videographers. WE ARE STORYTELLERS. We specialize in using digital and film mediums to create handcrafted wedding films that tell the story of the most important day of your life. Every couple has a unique and beautiful story, full of its own romance, with its own ups and downs, and its own twists and turns. WE ARE ARTISTS. A camera is simply a tool for filling in a canvas but having the vision to artistically paint that canvas requires an artistic gift coupled with years of practice. We intimately pair each image from that canvas with the sounds of laughter and tears, heart felt words, and emotional music from your wedding day and then the canvas truly comes to life. WE ARE PASSIONATE. We are passionate about life, the people we share it with, and the stories that we tell. Every couple we meet is unique. We love hearing their stories and capturing the moments that make their wedding day as unique as they are. It might be something as subtle as a heart-felt smile glanced across the room or something as significant as the couple’s first kiss as husband and wife. We are passionate about capturing and sharing the stories that our couples share with us. Our passion is using the art of cinema to capture the beauty and emotion of every special moment on the best day of your life so that you can see, hear, and feel that day for every day to come.

Description: 72photos is a photo management and sharing service allowing users to upload, edit, share and backup their photos online.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: 72photos is an innovative photo management and sharing service that allows users to upload, edit, share and backup their photos online. No fee is required to use 72photos and pro accounts are available to users that can provide them with additional space and bandwidth for a small yearly fee. Every user on 72photos has a personal online profile showcasing photos and galleries from their 72photos account. Users have the option to set extensive permissions on their profile, photos and galleries to control exactly what others can see. 72photos also features an in-suite set of photo manipulation and editing tools that allow users to complete tasks such as: red-eye removal, cropping, rotating, black/white, sepia and much more. In addition to editing tools, all user photos are versioned, which allows them to revert back to the original at any time. Other features of 72photos include advanced organizational tools such as real-time searching, tagging, and filtering photos by the camera that was used to take them. Sharing options are also provided to allow users to post their photos directly to Facebook, Myspace and other social networking sites as well as embeddable widgets for use on their personal blog or website.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Software
